  <summary date="2020-06-09T15:44:48Z" status="Introduced in House">SFC Richard Stayskal Military Medical Accountability Act of 2019

This bill allows claims to be brought against the United States&#160;for damages relating to the personal injury or death of a member of the Armed Forces arising out of a negligent or wrongful act or omission in providing medical, dental, or related health care functions at a military medical treatment facility. However, the bill does not apply to care provided at a medical treatment location deployed in an area of armed combat.</summary>
